2014-03-06 05:28:33	TheBrayn	I have a prompt with two lines, how can I make the rprompt be in the first line?
2014-03-06 05:31:42	vifon	You can't. You'll need to insert it into the regular prompt and pad its first line with spaces.
2014-03-06 05:32:07	TheBrayn	how can I pad it?
2014-03-06 05:32:27	vifon	Protip: don't do it. You'll suffer each and every time you resize the terminal window.
2014-03-06 05:32:41	TheBrayn	ok
2014-03-06 05:33:29	vifon	Just calculate how many spaces you need and insert them before the "rprompt". But don't. ;)
2014-03-06 05:33:45	vifon	Been there, done that.
